Roffman Miller Associates Inc. PA Has $482,000 Stake in Bristol-Myers Squibb Company (BMY)

					Posted by Rex Bailey on Jul 28th, 2017 // No Comments 


Tweet












Roffman Miller Associates Inc. PA decreased its position in  Bristol-Myers Squibb Company (NYSE:BMY) by 27.7% during the second quarter, Holdings Channel reports. The institutional investor  owned 8,645 shares of the biopharmaceutical company’s stock after selling 3,309 shares during the period. Roffman Miller Associates Inc. PA’s holdings in Bristol-Myers Squibb were worth $482,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
Several other institutional investors also recently made changes to their positions in BMY. Sciencast Management LP acquired a new stake in  Bristol-Myers Squibb during the fourth quarter valued at $480,000.  Seven Eight Capital LP acquired a new stake in  Bristol-Myers Squibb during the fourth quarter valued at $1,575,000.  Ancora Advisors LLC boosted its stake in  Bristol-Myers Squibb by 18.6% in the fourth quarter. Ancora Advisors LLC now owns 102,513 shares of the biopharmaceutical company’s stock valued at $5,991,000 after buying an additional 16,063 shares during the last quarter.  Ellington Management Group LLC acquired a new stake in  Bristol-Myers Squibb during the fourth quarter valued at $1,005,000.  Finally, Focused Wealth Management Inc boosted its stake in  Bristol-Myers Squibb by 11.8% in the fourth quarter. Focused Wealth Management Inc now owns 9,747 shares of the biopharmaceutical company’s stock valued at $570,000 after buying an additional 1,028 shares during the last quarter. 69.72% of the stock is owned by institutional investors and hedge funds. 


 Get Bristol-Myers Squibb Company alerts:



Bristol-Myers Squibb Company (BMY) opened at 54.24 on Friday. Bristol-Myers Squibb Company has a one year low of $46.01 and a one year high of $76.30. The company’s 50-day moving average price is $55.34 and its 200-day moving average price is $54.59. The firm has a market cap of $89.36 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 18.84 and a beta of 1.17. 




Bristol-Myers Squibb (NYSE:BMY) last issued its quarterly earnings results on Thursday, July 27th. The biopharmaceutical company reported $0.74 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, beating the consensus estimate of $0.73 by $0.01. Bristol-Myers Squibb had a return on equity of 31.86% and a net margin of 24.22%. The firm had revenue of $5.14 billion for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $5.09 billion. During the same period in the previous year, the company posted $0.69 earnings per share. The company’s quarterly revenue was up 5.6% compared to the same quarter last year.  On average, analysts anticipate that  Bristol-Myers Squibb Company will post $2.95 EPS for the current year. 
The company also recently declared a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Tuesday, August 1st. Investors of record on Friday, July 7th will be paid a dividend of $0.39 per share. The ex-dividend date is Wednesday, July 5th. This represents a $1.56 annualized dividend and a yield of 2.88%. Bristol-Myers Squibb’s dividend payout ratio  is 54.17%. 
